The '''Roger Crozier Saving Grace Award''' is one of the [[National Hockey League]]'s many [[National Hockey League awards|trophies]].  First handed out at the conclusion of the [[1999-2000 NHL season|1999-2000]] season, it is given to the [[goaltender]] with the best [[save percentage]], having played a minimum of 25 regular season games.  It is named for former [[Detroit Red Wings]] and [[Buffalo Sabres]] goaltender [[Roger Crozier]], who helped both teams reach the [[Stanley Cup]] finals.

Since the award's inception, [[Dallas Stars]] have won it on 3 occasions, while the [[Montreal Canadiens]] and the [[Minnesota Wild]] have each won it twice. Since the league began tracking save percentage as a statistic, the [[Buffalo Sabres]] and Montreal Canadiens have each finished atop the league 6 times.

The winner of the trophy is given $25,000 [[USD]] to donate to a youth hockey or other educational program of their choice.

== List of award recipients ==
* [[2006-07 NHL season|2006-07]] - [[Niklas Bäckström|Niklas Backstrom]], [[Minnesota Wild]]
* [[2005-06 NHL season|2005-06]] - [[Cristobal Huet]], [[Montreal Canadiens]]
* [[2004-05 NHL season|2004-05]] - ''No winner due to the [[2004-05 NHL lockout]]''
* [[2003-04 NHL season|2003-04]] - [[Dwayne Roloson]], Minnesota Wild
* [[2002-03 NHL season|2002-03]] - [[Marty Turco]], [[Dallas Stars]]
* [[2001-02 NHL season|2001-02]] - [[Jose Theodore]], Montreal Canadiens
* [[2000-01 NHL season|2000-01]] - [[Marty Turco]], Dallas Stars
* 1999-2000 - [[Ed Belfour]], Dallas Stars

== Previous Save Percentage Leaders ==
Listed below are goaltenders who led the league in save percentage prior to the creation of the Roger Crozier Saving Grace Award:
* [[1998-99 NHL season|1998-99]] - [[Dominik Hasek]], Buffalo Sabres **
* [[1997-98 NHL season|1997-98]] - Dominik Hasek, Buffalo Sabres
* [[1996-97 NHL season|1996-97]] - Dominik Hasek, Buffalo Sabres
* [[1995-96 NHL season|1995-96]] - Dominik Hasek, Buffalo Sabres
* [[1994-95 NHL season|1994-95]] - Dominik Hasek, Buffalo Sabres
* [[1993-94 NHL season|1993-94]] - Dominik Hasek, Buffalo Sabres
* [[1992-93 NHL season|1992-93]] - [[Curtis Joseph]], [[St. Louis Blues (hockey)|St. Louis Blues]]
* [[1991-92 NHL season|1991-92]] - [[Patrick Roy]], Montreal Canadiens
* [[1990-91 NHL season|1990-91]] - Ed Belfour, [[Chicago Blackhawks]]
* [[1989-90 NHL season|1989-90]] - Patrick Roy, Montreal Canadiens
* [[1988-89 NHL season|1988-89]] - Patrick Roy, Montreal Canadiens
* [[1987-88 NHL season|1987-88]] - Patrick Roy, Montreal Canadiens
* [[1986-87 NHL season|1986-87]] - [[Ron Hextall]], [[Philadelphia Flyers]]
* [[1985-86 NHL season|1985-86]] - [[Bob Froese]], Philadelphia Flyers
* [[1984-85 NHL season|1984-85]] - [[Warren Skorodenski]], Chicago Blackhawks
* [[1983-84 NHL season|1983-84]] - [[Roland Melanson]], [[New York Islanders]]
* [[1982-83 NHL season|1982-83]]* - Roland Melanson, New York Islanders

''* first season save percentage was recognized as an official NHL statistic''

''** has greatest save percentage in one season (93.7%)''

